Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Halve, peel, and finely chop @shallot{1%unit}. Zest @lime{1%unit} until you have 1 tsp zest, then halve. Peel outer layers from @lemongrass{1%unit} until you get to tender core. Finely mince core. Pick and finely chop enough @mint{¼%ounce} leaves to give you 1 TBSP.

Cut @Persian cucumber{1%unit} in half lengthwise, then slice into thin half-moons. Peel @carrots{4%unit}, then cut into 3-inch lengths. Cut each length into thin wedges. Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until lightly browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, a squeeze of lime juice, and up to half the @sriracha{2%tsp} (use less if you like it mild). Set aside.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @ground pork{10%ounce}, lemongrass, lime zest, shallot, @soy sauce{1%tbsp} (we sent more), half the mint, @Thai seasoning blend{1%tsp}, and remaining sriracha (to taste). Season with salt and pepper. Shape mixture into two evenly sized patties with your hands (they should be slightly wider than the buns).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add patties to pan and cook until browned and no longer pink in center, ~{4-5%minutes} per side. Meanwhile, split @brioche buns{2%unit} in half and place on another baking sheet. Toast in oven until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}. Once carrots are done, sprinkle mint leaves (to taste) and a squeeze of lime juice over wedges.

Spread sriracha mayo on buns, then fill with patties, cucumber, and any remaining mint (to taste). Serve with carrot fries to the side.

